<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph box="[0,1273,531,849]" pageId="2" pageNumber="6" type="mainText">
Note: This species, previously considered as a variety of 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Dicranaceae" genus="Campylopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dicranales" pageId="2" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="surinamensis">
C. surinamensis (
<authority pageId="2" pageNumber="6">
Frahm 
<date pageId="2" pageNumber="6">1980</date>
</authority>
)
</taxonomicName>
, was later reinstated as a distinct species (Frahm 1991). It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Dicranaceae" genus="Campylopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dicranales" pageId="2" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="surinamensis">C. surinamensis</taxonomicName>
by the equally foliate stems with wide-spreading leaves; moreover the leaves are more slenderly acuminate with a narrow, keeled apex; the alar cells are more inflated and coloured forming distinct auricles, whereas in 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Dicranaceae" genus="Campylopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dicranales" pageId="2" pageNumber="6" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="surinamensis">C. surinamensis</taxonomicName>
the auricles are often indistinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
